H0.text: Taphephobia is the fear of losing your teeth. True

H1.text: Taphephobia is the fear of losing your teeth. The fear of being buried alive

H2.text: Taphephobia is the fear of losing your teeth. A type of dental anxiety

H3.text: Taphephobia is the fear of losing your teeth. False

A4.text: Taphophobia (from Greek τάφος – taphos, 'grave, tomb' and φόβος – phobos, 'fear') is an abnormal phobia of being buried alive as a result of being incorrectly pronounced dead.

A5.text: In 1905, the English reformer William Tebb collected accounts of premature burial.
